Governor Aminu Tambuwal of Sokoto State has declared his intention to contest the 2023 presidential election on the platform of the Peoples Democratic Party.Tambuwal made this known after a high-level stakeholder meeting in Sokoto. The former House of Representatives Speaker said he was not only well prepared but also ready to fix the numerous problems of the country as president of Nigeria.He said he had distinguished himself not only as governor but as lawmaker without any blemish or corruption tag.Tambuwal joins Dele Momodu and Governor Mohammed Bala of Bauchi State as the three PDP members to have publicly confirmed their desire to contest next yearâ€™s presidential election.